definition: parking spot/unloading point/garage place/stand for taxi
car/vehicle/CL:輛|辆[liang4]/machine/to shape with a lathe/Kangxi radical 159
position/location/place/seat/classifier for people (honorific)/classifier for binary bits (e.g. 十六位 16-bit or 2 bytes)/(physics) potential

sentences.english: Paint a parking space in the living room.
sentences.chinese: 在自家客厅用油漆画一个停车位。

sentences.english: Monthly paid rent, car park available.
sentences.chinese: 房租月付，带停车位，长短期租住皆可。

sentences.english: From the parking lot, visitors descend a tree-lined staircase down a steep slope.
sentences.chinese: 参观者可以从停车位走下绿树成荫的楼梯，进入斜坡。

sentences.english: No parking spaces will be provided to the athletes.
sentences.chinese: 本处不会提供车位供各运动员使用。

sentences.english: Parking is available on a first-come, first-served basis along tree-lined Kai Yuan Road.
sentences.chinese: 停车位是沿着开元路上，总是先到先得。

sentences.english: We plan to rent some of them out at the hourly rates.
sentences.chinese: 我们打算把一部分车位按小时收费租出去。

sentences.english: She reversed the car into the parking space.
The above Car Park shall only be used for car parking purpose.
sentences.chinese: 租方不得将上述车位或任何部份转让或分租与他人。

sentences.english: She maneuvered her car into a narrow parking space with ease.
sentences.chinese: 她轻松地把车驶进了一个狭小的车位。

sentences.english: It will probably be easier to reverse into that parking space.
sentences.chinese: 把车倒进那个停车位大概会容易一点。

sentences.english: Its driveway is lined with the white Ambassador sedans used by government officials.
sentences.chinese: 停车位上停放着供政府官员使用的白色大使轿子。

sentences.english: It's difficult to find a parking space.
Parking spaces in parking garages in Brazil were split in half.
sentences.chinese: 在巴西，停车场的停车位被一分为二。

sentences.english: Drivers in London fork out the most for a monthly unreserved space.
sentences.chinese: 伦敦的司机每个月为非专用停车位付的钱最多。

sentences.english: So I had to drive, so they gave me a parking.
sentences.chinese: 所以我必须开车，所以他们给我了一个车位。

definition: to pull up (stop one's vehicle)/to park/(of a machine) to stop working/to stall
property/real estate/abbr. for 物業管理|物业管理[wu4 ye4 guan3 li3], property management
to park (a car etc)/to moor (a boat etc)/to leave sth (in a place)
car or other vehicle (bicycle, truck etc)
